$ SQL Server: @@options

`@@options` is a bit field that keeps track of which option was → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/statements/set[`set`] to `on` or `off`.

{ decoding the bit field

  The following query can be used to quickly assess which options were set to on and off.

  gh|about-MSSQL|/t-sql/variables/@@/options/decode-bits.sql||

}
